def time_delta(func, *args, **kwargs): 
    start_time = time.time()
    func(*args, **kwargs)
    end_time = time.time()
    
    return end_time-start_time
In [5]:
def merge_two_dicts(dict1, dict2):
    dict3 = defaultdict(list)
    items = list(dict1.items())+list(dict2.items())

    for k, v in items:
        for item in v:
            dict3[k].append(item)
    return dict3

def read_task_1(file_name, header, sep='|'):
    result = {}
    data = np.genfromtxt(file_name, delimiter=sep, skip_header=1)
    for i, name in enumerate(header):
        result[name] = data[:,i]
    return result
In [7]:
def read_task_2_3(file_name, sep='|', test_size=.3, bias=True):
    data = np.genfromtxt(file_name, delimiter=sep, skip_header=1)
    
    train_idx = np.random.choice(range(data.shape[0]), size=int(data.shape[0]*(1 - test_size)), replace = False)
    test_idx  = np.array([i for i in range(data.shape[0]) if i not in train_idx])
    
    if bias:
        X_train = np.hstack((data[train_idx,:-1], 
                             np.ones((train_idx.shape[0], 1))
                            ))
        X_test =  np.hstack((data[test_idx,:-1],
                         np.ones((test_idx.shape[0], 1))
                        ))
    else:
        X_train = data[train_idx,:-1]
        X_test = data[test_idx,:-1]
        
    y_train = data[train_idx,-1] 
    
   
    y_test = data[test_idx,-1]
    return X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test

    plt.yticks(range(corr_mtrx.shape[1]), fontsize=9)

$y$ $x$ $y_i=\sum_{j=1}^m{w_jx_{ij}}+w_{0}+\epsilon_i$, . $x_0=1$ (bais). :

$$y=Xw+\epsilon$$ :

  • $w$ $-$
  • $X$ $-$ $n$ $m+1$ ( : +1?)
  • $\epsilon$ $-$

__ "" ?__

,

\begin{array}{rcl}\mathcal{L}\left( X, {y}, {w} \right) &=& \frac{1}{2n} \sum_{i=1}^n \left(y_i - {w}^\text{T} {x}_i\right)^2 \\ &=& \frac{1}{2n} \left\| {y} - X {w} \right\|_2^2 \\ &=& \frac{1}{2n} \left({y} - X {w}\right)^\text{T} \left({y} - X {w}\right) \end{array}

$w$ :

\begin{array}{rcl} \frac{\partial \mathcal{L}}{\partial {w}} &=& \frac{1}{2n} \left( {y}^{\text{T}} {y} -2{y}^{\text{T}} {X} {w} + {w}^{\text{T}} {X}^{\text{T}} {X} {w}\right) \\ &=& \frac{1}{2n} \left(-2 {X}^{\text{T}} {y} + 2{X}^{\text{T}} {X} {w}\right) \end{array}\begin{array}{rcl} \frac{\partial \mathcal{L}}{\partial {w}} = 0 &\Leftrightarrow& \frac{1}{2n} \left(-2 {X}^{\text{T}} {y} + 2{X}^{\text{T}} {X} {w}\right) = 0 \\ &\Leftrightarrow& -{X}^{\text{T}} {y} + {X}^{\text{T}} {X} {w} = 0 \\ &\Leftrightarrow& {X}^{\text{T}} {X} {w} = {X}^{\text{T}} {y} \\ \end{array}

$$ {w} = \left({X}^{\text{T}} {X}\right)^{-1} {X}^{\text{T}} {y}$$

def least_squares_weights(x, y): #     
    w = np.matmul(np.linalg.inv(np.matmul(x.T,x)),np.dot(x.T,y))
    return w

def MAError(y_true, y_predict): #  
    error = np.absolute(np.subtract(y_true,y_predict)).mean()
    #print('MAError = ',error)
    return error

def MSError(y_true, y_predict):
    error = np.square(np.subtract(y_true,y_predict)).mean()
    #print('MSError = ',error)
    return error

def RMSError(y_true, y_predict):
    error = np.sqrt(MSError(y_true,y_predict))
    #print('RMAError = ',error)
    return error

def R_square(y_true, y_predict):
    error = 1 - (np.square(np.subtract(y_true,y_predict))).sum()/(np.square(np.subtract(y_true,y_true.mean()))).sum()
    #print('R_square = ',error)
    return error

def all_metric(y_true, y_predict):
    d = {}
    d['MAE'] = [MAError(y_true, y_predict)] 
    d['MSE'] = [MSError(y_true, y_predict)] 
    d['RMSE'] = [RMSError(y_true, y_predict)]
    d['R_square'] = [R_square(y_true, y_predict)]
    return d

# TESTS
assert round(MAError(y_true=Y_train, y_predict=Y_train_predict), 3) == 1.274, '   '
assert time_delta(MAError, Y_train, Y_train_predict) < 1.5, '   ,     '

assert round(MSError(y_true=Y_train, y_predict=Y_train_predict), 3) == 2.22, '   '

assert time_delta(R_square, Y_train, Y_train_predict) < 1.5, '   ,     '

$w$ . $\left({X}^{\text{T}} {X}\right)^{-1} {X}^{\text{T}} {y}$, $y$ .

, . , $w_i$ .

.

$$H_0: w_i=0 \\ H_1: w_i\not=0$$

$t$ $n-k$ $H_0$:

$$t=\frac{w_i}{se(w_i)}$$

,

  • $n$ $-$
  • $k$ $-$
  • $se(w_i)$ $-$ $w_i$

$se(w_i)$ - $\hat{Var}(w|X)$

$$\hat{Var}(w|X)=\hat\sigma^2({X}^{\text{T}} {X})^{-1}$$

, $\hat\sigma^2$ $\sigma^2$

$$\hat\sigma^2=\frac{RSS}{n-k}=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-wx_i)^2}{n-k}$$

, t- . $\text{p_value}$ :

$$\text{p_value}=2(1-cdf(t, df=n-k))$$

def variance_matrix(X, y_true, y_predict): #  
    sigma_2 = (np.square(y_true - y_predict).sum())/(X.shape[0]-X.shape[1])
    variance = sigma_2*np.linalg.inv(np.matmul(X.T,X))
    return variance

vcov =  variance_matrix (X_train_new[:,:], Y_train, Y_train_predict)

def p_values(t, df): #    :   p_values = 
    result = 2*(1 - stats.t.cdf(abs(t),df))    # = 2(1 - cdf(|t|,df)).  |t|!

def stochastic_gradient_step(w, X, y):
    grad = 2/(w.shape[0])*(np.matmul(X.T,np.matmul(X,w)-y)) #     
    return grad                                          #  " "
                                              #  -     
                                              #  L  w

def fit(X, y, analytical_w, random_state=42, iters=100, batch_size=10, learning_rate=0.05, plot=True):
    random_gen = np.random.RandomState(random_state)
    errors = []
    
    
    #   
    size, dim = X.shape

    #   
    w = random_gen.rand(dim)
    
    weights_history = w
    colors = [plt.get_cmap('gist_rainbow')(i) for i in np.linspace(0,1,dim)]
    
    # plt 
    if plot:
        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))
        ax1 = fig.add_subplot(221)
        ax2 = fig.add_subplot(222)
        ax3 = fig.add_subplot(212)
        fig.suptitle('Gradient descent')
        
        
    for _ in range(iters):  
        #    
        rand_indices = random_gen.choice(size, batch_size)
        X_ = X[rand_indices]
        y_ = y[rand_indices]

        #  
        grad = stochastic_gradient_step(w, X_, y_)
        assert type(grad) == np.ndarray, ' '
        assert len(grad.shape) == 1, '   '
        assert grad.shape[0] == len(w), '      '
        
        w   -= grad * learning_rate
        
        #  
        weights_history = np.vstack((weights_history, w))
        
        # error
        predict = least_squares_predict(w, X)
        errors.append(R_square(y, predict))
        
        if plot:
            ax1.clear()            
            ax1.plot(range(dim), analytical_w, 'bo-', label='Analytical solution')
            ax1.plot(range(dim), w, 'ro-', label='Gradient solution')
            ax1.legend(loc="upper left")
            ax1.set_title('weights')
            ax1.set_ylabel(r'$\bar \beta$')
            ax1.set_xlabel('weight ID')
            
            
            ax2.plot(range(_+1), errors, 'g-')
            ax2.set_title('R_square')
            ax2.set_xlabel('itarations')
            
            ax3.plot(weights_history)
            ax3.set_title('update weights')
            ax3.set_ylabel('value')
            ax3.set_xlabel('itarations')
            fig.set(facecolor = 'white')
            
            time.sleep(0.3)
            fig.canvas.draw()   
            
    return w, analytical_w

def stochastic_gradient_step(w, X, y, alpha=1, l1_ratio=0.5):
    grad = 2/(w.shape[0])*(np.matmul(X.T,np.matmul(X,w)-y)) + alpha*l1_ratio + alpha*(1-l1_ratio)*w
    
    return grad

def probability(W, X): #   (   ,    
    result = 1/(1 + np.exp(-np.matmul(X,W)))  #.     -  .
    return result

prob = probability(W, X_train)

def binary_class_prediction(W, X, threshold =.5):
    prob =  probability(W, X)
    result = np.zeros([prob.shape[0],])  #     
    for i in range(len(prob)):           #    
        #print(i)
        if prob[i] > threshold:
            result[i] = 1
        else:
            result[i] = 0
    return result

Y_train_predict = binary_class_prediction(W, X_train)
Y_test_predict = binary_class_prediction(W, X_test)

def binary_accuracy(y_true, y_predict):
    result = ((0 == y_predict - y_true)*1).sum()/len(y_true) #  accuracy   2
    print('binary_accuracy = ', result*100,'%')
    return result
